-- Source truth: ScoreProject/DawProjectSource contain authored intent only.
-- Derived truth: Semantic/Rated/Planned/Kernel facts are phase outputs.
-- Edit truth: EditEventRef is the only UI/host edit vocabulary.
-- Choice ownership: every kind field above names one visit_* / dispatch_* owner.
-- Phase boundaries:
--   validate_source_project: answers whether source is coherent.
--   resolve_*: answers identity, reference, time-normalization, asset-shape facts.
--   rate_*: answers when each binding is known: literal/init/block/sample/event/voice.
--   plan_*: answers buffer allocation, scheduling, launch tables, routing order.
--   kernel_*: answers concrete compiled types, quotes, functions, and ABI handles.
-- Runtime seals:
--   daw_audio_callback consumes LiveCommandRef and PlannedStep facts only.
--   It must not inspect ScoreProject or DawProjectSource.
--   Plugin/audio/device effects occur through runtime regions or sealed externs.
-- No internal status-code soup: internal outcomes are continuations; i32 only at funcs.
-- No pass-through regions: every listed region owns an encoding, hides a statechart,
-- answers a knowledge question, or seals an ABI/effect boundary.
